  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nPlease note that this is an issue tracker reserved for bug reports and feature requests.\r\n\r\nFor general questions please use the gitter channel or the Ethereum stack exchange at https://ethereum.stackexchange.com.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: ` 1.9.12-stable`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nI should be able to connect to remote node on ec2 instance\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n```\r\nconnectex: A connection attempt failed because the connected party did not properly respond after a period of time, or established connection failed because connected host has failed to respond.\r\n```\r\n\r\nI have an ec2 instance which is running geth, I ran it using \r\n``` geth --syncmode \"light\" -ws --shh -wsapi shh```\r\nBut when I use the ip of the ec2 instance, I can't connect to the instance, I'm running a go program which connects and generates key pair, I have enabled all ports on the instance and allowed all incoming traffic, But I can't connect to it, But when I ran a normal server which sends a response, It works and when I ran the program locally on the instance it worked, So I don't know what's wrong please help me.\r\n\r\n```\r\npackage main\r\n\r\nimport (\r\n\t\"context\"\r\n\t\"fmt\"\r\n\t\"log\"\r\n\r\n\t\"github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/whisper/shhclient\"\r\n)\r\n\r\nfunc main() {\r\n\tclient, err := shhclient.Dial(\"ws://ip_of_ec2:8546\")\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\tlog.Fatal(err)\r\n\t}\r\n\tkeyID, err := client.NewKeyPair(context.Background())\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\tlog.Fatal(err)\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tfmt.Println(keyID) // 0ec5cfe4e215239756054992dbc2e10f011db1cdfc88b9ba6301e2f9ea1b58d2\r\n\tpublicKey, err := client.PublicKey(context.Background(), keyID)\r\n\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\tlog.Fatal(err)\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tfmt.Println(publicKey)\r\n\r\n}\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n",
